]]''||  || [[German language|German]] || ''Twilight of the Gods'' || [[opera]] by [[Richard Wagner]]\n|-\n|[[Gurrelieder]]||  || [[German language|German]] || Songs of Gurre || [[oratorio]] by [[Arnold Schoenberg]]\n|-\n|[[Hagia Sophia]]|| \u1f0d\u03b3\u03b9\u03b1 \u03a3\u03bf\u03c6\u03af\u03b1 || [[Greek language|Greek]] || Divine Wisdom || [[Byzantine]] [[dome]]-[[church (building)|church]] (now a [[mosque]]), located in [[Istanbul]], [[Turkey]]\n|-\n|''[[Harakiri (1962 film)|Harakiri]]''|| \u8179\u5207\u308a || [[Japanese language|Japanese]] || [[Harakiri]]/cutting the belly || film by [[Masaki Kobayashi]]\n|-\n|''[[H\u00e4xan]]''||  || [[Swedish language|Swedish]] || ''Witches'' || film by [[Benjamin Christensen]]\n|-\n|[[Heimskringla]]||  || [[Old Norse]] || The World-Circle || [[Kings' saga]] by [[Snorri Sturluson]]\n|-\n|''[[Hiroshima mon amour]]''||  || [[French language|French]] || ''Hiroshima My Love'' || film directed by [[Alain Resnais]]\n|-\n|''[[Huis clos]]''||  || [[French language|French]] || ''In Camera'' || [[play (theatre)|play]] by [[Jean-Paul Sartre]]\n|-\n|[[Ich will]]||  || [[German language|German]] || I want || song by [[Rammstein]]\n|-\n|''[[Ikiru]]''|| \u751f\u304d\u308b || [[Japanese language|Japanese]] || ''To Live'' || film directed by [[Akira Kurosawa]]\n|-\n|''[[Il trovatore]]''||  || [[Italian language|Italian]] || ''The Troubadour'' || [[opera]] by [[Giuseppe Verdi]]\n|-\n|''[[Iliad|Ilias]]''|| \u1f38\u03bb\u03b9\u03ac\u03c2 || [[Ancient Greek]] || \"Trojan\" or \"[[Troad|Troas]]\" || [[epic poem]], attributed to [[Homer]]\n|-\n|[[Jeux d'enfants]]||  || [[French language|French]] || Children's Games || symphonic [[suite (music)|suite]] by [[Georges Bizet]]\n|-\n|[[Jewang Ungi]]|| \uc81c\uc655\uc6b4\uae30 || [[Korean language|Korean]] || Rhymed Chronicles of Sovereigns || [[poem]] by [[Yi Seung-hyu]]\n|-\n|[[Kaaba]]|| \u0627\u0644\u0643\u0639\u0628\u0629 || [[Arabic]] || The Cube || most sacred site in [[Islam]], located in [[Mecca]]