 to Rome]|url=http://archive.168.am/am/articles/11036|work=168.am (168 Hours Online)|date=26 August 2007|language=hy|quote=\u053f\u0572\u0566\u056b \u0561\u0574\u0565\u0576 \u057f\u0561\u0580\u056b \u0561\u0575\u0581\u0565\u056c\u0578\u0582\u0574 \u0567 \u0574\u0578\u057f 40.000 \u0566\u0562\u0578\u057d\u0561\u0577\u0580\u057b\u056b\u056f: = Around 40,000 tourists visit the island annually.|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304083203/http://archive.168.am/am/articles/11036|archivedate=4 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"turismovenezia\">{{cite web|title=Monastero Mechitarista|url=http://www.turismovenezia.it/Venezia/Monastero-Mechitarista-6180.html|website=turismovenezia.it|publisher=Provincia di Venezia|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170131145152/http://www.turismovenezia.it/Venezia/Monastero-Mechitarista-6180.html|archivedate=31 January 2017}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"newarmenia\">{{cite journal|last1=Deolen|first1=A.|title=The Mekhitarists|journal=[[The New Armenia]]|date=1919|volume=11|issue=7|page=[https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=coo.31924093298036;view=1up;seq=308 104]}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Mouradyan\">{{cite journal|last=Mouradyan|first=Anahit|title=\u0540\u0561\u0575 \u057f\u057a\u0561\u0563\u0580\u0578\u0582\u0569\u0575\u0561\u0576 500-\u0561\u0574\u0575\u0561\u056f\u0568 [The 500th Anniversary of the Armenian Book-Printing]|journal=[[Patma-Banasirakan Handes]]|volume=\u2116 1|date=2012|issue=1|pages=58\u201359|url=http://hpj.asj-oa.am/5731/|language=hy}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"T\u00f6l\u00f6lyan\">{{cite book|last1=T\u00f6l\u00f6lyan|first1=Khachig|editor1-last=Ember|editor1-first=Melvin|editor2-last=Ember|editor2-first=Carol R.|editor3-last=Skoggard|editor3-first=Ian|editor1-link=Melvin Ember|editor2-link=Carol R. Ember|title=Encyclopedia of Diasporas|chapter=Armenian Diaspora|date=2005|publisher=[[Springer Science+Business Media|Springer]]|isbn=978-0-306-48321-9|page=40}}</ref>\n\n}}\n\n==Bibliography==\n===Books on 